{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781216712859,"sessionID":"ses_14746d194ffeF6CRS45EtE7lwx","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_gx6y84iq","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"README.md","content":"Usage:\nTo use the temperature-conversion CLI tool, run the following command:\n\ntemperature-converter --convert-from <from_unit> --convert-to <to_unit> --value <value>\n\nWhere:\n<from_unit> is one of celsius, fahrenheit, or kelvin\n<to_unit> is one of celsius, fahrenheit, or kelvin\n<value> is the temperature value to convert\n\nExamples:\nConvert 25 degrees Celsius to Fahrenheit:\ntemperature-converter --convert-from celsius --convert-to fahrenheit --value 25\n\nConvert 32 degrees Fahrenheit to Celsius:\ntemperature-converter --convert-from fahrenheit --convert-to celsius --value 32\n\nConvert 0 degrees Celsius to Kelvin:\ntemperature-converter --convert-from celsius --convert-to kelvin --value 0\n\nInstallation:\nTo install the package, run:\npip install temperature-converter\n\nAlternatively, if you're using the source code, install it via:\npip install -e .\n\nNote:\nThis tool currently supports the following conversions:\n- Celsius to Fahrenheit\n- Fahrenheit to Celsius\n- Celsius to Kelvin\n\nAdditional conversions may be added in future updates."},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/scratch/spike-pi-form-adequacy-gate/A_live/ws_4/README.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"scratch/spike-pi-form-adequacy-gate/A_live/ws_4/README.md","time":{"start":1781216712851,"end":1781216712858}},"id":"prt_eb8ca1885001acef3Oubu6wz29","sessionID":"ses_14746d194ffeF6CRS45EtE7lwx","messageID":"msg_eb8c6b26d001B0ILPjBIX0rG1c"}}
